data.name: High-Protein Chicken Burrito with Salsa
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty, high-protein burrito filled with grilled chicken, fresh veggies, and zesty salsa, wrapped in a gluten-free tortilla.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill or skillet over medium-high heat.
Season the chicken breast with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Grill for about 6-7 minutes on each side until fully cooked. Let it rest for a few minutes, then slice it.
In a large bowl, combine black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, chopped cilantro, lime juice, and a pinch of salt.
Warm the gluten-free tortillas in a skillet for about 30 seconds on each side until pliable.
Layer the grilled chicken, bean mixture, shredded cheese, and avocado slices on each tortilla.
Drizzle with salsa, fold in the sides, and roll tightly to form a burrito. Serve with extra salsa on the side.
data.detailedName: High-Protein Chicken Burrito with Fresh Salsa
